{"lemma":"أَدْنَى","slug":"أَدْنَى","root":"د.ن.#","root_slug":"د-ن-_","root_link":"/words/roots/د-ن-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"أَدْنَى","root":"دنو","pos":"N","occurrence_count":12},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":0},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n13225","n13237"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%92%D9%86%D9%8E%D9%89"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n13225","headword_ar":"اِدَّنَى","root":"dnw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aid~inaA='N","text_ar":"اِدِّنَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 1."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n13237","headword_ar":"اَدْنَى","root":"dnw","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Nearer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nearest;"},{"kind":"text","text":"opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqoSaY","text_ar":"اَقْصَى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dunoyaA","text_ar":"دُنْيَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, TA;) in which the [radical]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"is changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuloyaA","text_ar":"عُلْيَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quSoyaA","text_ar":"قُصْيَا"},{"kind":"text","text":": (ISd, TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buqowaY","text_ar":"بُقْوَى"},{"kind":"text","text":":) [the pl. of the masc. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adaAnK","text_ar":"اَدَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adonawona","text_ar":"اَدْنَوْنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the latter in the accus. and gen."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adonayoni","text_ar":"اَدْنَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and] the pl. of the fem.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dunFY","text_ar":"دُنًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, TA,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kubarN","text_ar":"كُبَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuboraY","text_ar":"كُبْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SugarN","text_ar":"صُغَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SugoraY","text_ar":"صُغْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, TA;) said by some to be extr. and strange [in respect of usage]; and El-Mutanebbee has been blamed for using it; (MF, TA;) but in the case referred to he has used"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~unaY","text_ar":"الدُّنَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~unoyaA","text_ar":"الدُّنْيَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", [not as a pl.,] suppressing the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"by poetic license. (TA.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gulibati Alr~uwmu fiY A^adonaY","text_ar":"غُلِبَتِ الرُّومُ فِى اَدْنَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aroDi","text_ar":"الاَرْضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur xxx. 1 and 2,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Greeks have been overcome in the nearer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nearest, part of the land."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, Jel.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljamorapu Ald~unoyaA","text_ar":"الجَمْرَةُ الدُّنْيَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The nearest heap of pebbles;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the heap of pebbles nearest to Minè."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [See art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jmr","text_ar":"جمر"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) And"},{"kind":"page_break","n":922},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~amaA='u Ald~unoyaA","text_ar":"السَّمَا=ءُ الدُّنْيَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The nearest heaven;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the lowest;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the heaven that is the nearest to us:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA:) also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samaA='u Ald~unoyaA","text_ar":"سَمَا=ءُ الدُّنْيَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the heaven of the present world;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as will be seen from what follows]. (TA.) See also exs. of the fem. in the paragraph commencing with the words"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa A@bonu","text_ar":"هُوَ ا@بْنُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eam~K dinoYK","text_ar":"عَمٍّ دِنْىٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in four places. ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Former,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"first;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fore,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foremost;"},{"kind":"text","text":"opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=xirN","text_ar":"ا=خِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [Hence,] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqiytuhu A^adonaY daniY~K","text_ar":"لَقِيتُهُ اَدْنَى دَنِىٍّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adonaY danFA","text_ar":"اَدْنَى دَنًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA, [in the CK, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AdnY dan~Y`","text_ar":"ادنى دَنّىٰ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AdnY daniY~K","text_ar":"ادنى دَنِىٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I met him the first thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adonaY Alfami","text_ar":"اَدْنَى الفَمِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The fore,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foremost, part of the mouth."},{"kind":"text","text":"] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~unoyaA","text_ar":"الدُّنْيَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~aAru Ald~unoyaA","text_ar":"الدَّارُ الدُّنْيَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHayaApu Ald~unoyaA","text_ar":"الحَيَاةُ الدُّنْيَا"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The former dwelling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"life;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the present world,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"life,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state of existence"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA=xirapu","text_ar":"الا=خِرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K:) [or] it is so called because of its nearness: (T, S:) [and may be rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the sublunary abode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the inferior abode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. It also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The enjoyments, blessings,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good, of the present world,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"life; worldly blessings"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prosperity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.] And sometimes it is with tenween, (K, TA,) when used indeterminately: (TA:) [thus,] IAar mentions the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA lahu dunoyFA wa laA A=xirapN","text_ar":"مَا لَهُ دُنْيًا وَ لَا ا=خِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has none of the enjoyments,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blessings, of the present world, nor"},{"kind":"text","text":"in prospect"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any enjoyments,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blessings, of the world to come"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; with tenween. (M, TA.) And you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAEa dunoyaAhu biA=xiratihi","text_ar":"بَاعَ دُنْيَاهُ بِا=خِرَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He purchased his enjoyments of the present world at the expense of his enjoyments of the world to come"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Z, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byE","text_ar":"بيع"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aabonu Ald~unoyaA","text_ar":"اَبْنُ الدُّنْيَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The rich man."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bnY","text_ar":"بنى"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"More,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most, apt, fit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proper:"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus in the Kur [xxxiii. 59], in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*`lika A^adonaY A^ano yuEarafona","text_ar":"ذٰلِكَ اَدْنَى اَنْ يُعَرَفْنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That will be more,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most, apt, fit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proper, that they may be known"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Ksh, Mgh;) i. e., that they may be known to be free women, as distinguished from female slaves, who did not cover their faces. (Jel.) ―         -b4-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Less"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in number"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quantity"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.], and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"least"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"therein"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akovaru","text_ar":"اَكْثَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA A^adonaY mino *`lika walaAA^akovara","text_ar":"وَلَا اَدْنَى مِنْ ذٰلِكَ وَلَااَكْثَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [lviii. 8], means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Nor less in number than that, nor more in number."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walanu*iyqan~ahumo mina A@loEa*aAbi A@loA^adonaY duwna A@loEa*aAbi A@loA^akobari","text_ar":"وَلَنُذِيقَنَّهُمْ مِنَ ا@لْعَذَابِ ا@لْاَدْنَى دُونَ ا@لْعَذَابِ ا@لْاَكْبَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [xxxii. 21, lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And we will assuredly make them to taste of the smaller punishment besides the greater punishment"},{"kind":"text","text":"], means, accord. to Zj, whatever punishment is inflicted in the present world and the punishment of the world to come. (M.) ―         -b5-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Worse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inferior"},{"kind":"text","text":"in quality,] and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"worst;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"more,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most, low, ignoble, base, vile, mean,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"weak;"},{"kind":"text","text":"opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayorN","text_ar":"خَيْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) It is said in the Kur [ii. 58],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atasotabodiluwna A@l~a*iY huwa","text_ar":"اَتَسْتَبْدِلُونَ ا@لَّذِى هُوَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adonaY biA@l~a*iY huwa xayorN","text_ar":"اَدْنَى بِا@لَّذِى هُوَ خَيْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Will ye take in exchange that which is worse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inferior, for that which is better?"},{"kind":"text","text":"or], accord. to Zj, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that which is less in value"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for that which is better"},{"kind":"text","text":"]?"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AdnY","text_ar":"ادنى"},{"kind":"text","text":"being thus, without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":": Fr says that it is here from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~anaA='apN","text_ar":"الدَّنَا=ءَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and Zuheyr El-Kurkubee [or (accord. to some) El-Furkubee] read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adonaA^u","text_ar":"اَدْنَاُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","S","K","T","M"]}]}}